@NODE Package "M-Tag Package"

The M-Tag package is a suite of programs which make file tagging a breeze
with DLG. Included in the package are:

    @{"M-TagFS       " Link "M-TagFS.guide/MAIN"} Full screen file tagger. Biggest componant.
    @{"M-Tag         " Link "M-Tag.guide/MAIN"} Single area list formatted file tagger.
    @{"M-Batch       " Link "M-Batch.guide/MAIN"} Full screen/List formatted batch list editor.
    @{"M-Scan        " Link "M-Scan.guide/MAIN"} File scanner. Scans for new files, or a pattern match.
    @{"M-Support     " Link "M-Support.guide/MAIN"} Support program. Has 3 functions:
                       - Update the #?.fd files after a download.
                       - Replaces the standard single file tag command.
                       - Produces the area list used by M-TagFS and M-Scan.

To make effective use of the M-Tag package, you need to make use of all these
programs. In the unregistered shareware form, there is still functionality.
M-Batch will automatically go into line mode for non-registered users.

Each program is fully functional to all users of level 255.

Each program looks after the special CD data file. This data file is used to
update the #?.fd files in situations where the file has an incorrect filenote
(mainly CD's).

While all programs have been released in this single package, upgrades to
individual programs may be distributed separately.


@ENDNODE

@NODE general "General set-up"

This package requires a script file to be used for downloading files. This
script file should be used for ALL downloading which may involve the standard
DLG batch downloading.

To set this up, edit the command for downloading to use the included menu
script 'File_DnLd.BAT'. The script file can be put in either the
'DLGConfig:Batch/' directory or the 'DLGConfig:Master/' directory.

Follow specific instillation directions for all the programs in this suit.

For those un-initiated in how command parameters are listed, the following
will be required reading!

When a command option is sorrounded by []'s, it means it is optional.

       eg: M-Support UPDATE [INFORM] means the INFORM keyword is optional.

When something is sorrounded by {}'s it means replace it with the appropriate
string.

       eg: M-TagFS.HLP.{language} means replace the word 'language' with an
                                  appropriate replacement such as 'english'

@ENDNODE

@NODE Magic " Why not MagicFile etc."

MagicFile and MagicScan are similar in function to M-TagFS and M-Scan.

These programs are quite good, but I beleive that the M-Tag package provides
a better solution.

M-TagFS has more features, and has many sysop configurable options.

M-Scan offers more flexibility with full wildcards, and runs faster when
wildcards are not used (as in MagicScan).

The M-Tag package provides a total file tagging system, with complete batch
editing included.

@ENDNODE

